main event: Project TWINKLE was initiated to investigate aerial phenomena in New Mexico, focusing on reports of unexplained light phenomena, including green fireballs.
interesting points: The investigation revealed that most aerial sightings can be attributed to man-made objects, such as balloons and aircraft,Reports indicated that personnel from Los Alamos frequently reported unusual aerial phenomena,Despite the reports, observations during significant meteor showers were minimal,During the study period, several individuals reported sightings of fireballs and strange objects, yet little concrete data was gathered from the investigations.
sighted object: various unidentified aerial phenomena, including bright objects and fireballs
location: Holloman Air Force Base, New Mexico, USA
witness description: personnel from Los Alamos and other military stations
